article.headline: ETSU 76, Marshall 72
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- Kevin Tiggs scored a career-high 31 points to lead East Tennessee State to a 76-72 victory over Marshall on Tuesday night. Tiggs hit a 3-point shot to give ETSU a 67-65 lead with 2:15 remaining and then added a layup for a 69-65 lead with 1:26 left. The Buccaneers (4-3) iced the game on Mike Smith's two free throws with 6 seconds remaining. Tiggs, a senior, was 13 of 18 from the floor, including two 3-pointers. He has scored 81 points in three career games against Marshall. Smith added 16 points for the Buccaneers. Markel Humphrey led Marshall (2-4) with 14 points. Damier Pitts added 11 points and Tirrell Baines scored 10 points and had 10 rebounds.
